request.description:
This API endpoint is used to create a new assessment for a department. It sends an HTTP POST request to the specified URL: `{{baseUrl}}{{mobileAPIversion}}/addAssessmentScale`.

### Request Payload

``` json
{
   "departmentEId": "",
   "assessmentDesc": "Name of the Assessment",
   "assessmentScaleTypeCd": "GENRL",
   "items": [
      {
         "displayTxt": "Assessment Question description",
         "resultTypeEId": "sfsafsgwefvbtga",
         "dropDownList": [
        {
          "displayTxt": "<option1>"
        },
        {
          "displayTxt": "<option2>"
        }
       ]
      }
   ]
}

 ```

`departmentEId`\- the unique ID of th department for which the assessment has to be created. The value for this is obtained from getDepartment API mentioned above.

`assessmentDesc`\- defines the name of the assessment

`assessmentScaleTypeCd`\- use 'GENRL' as the code to define the general assessment.

`items`\- array of objects indicating the assessment items containing the name of the assessment item as `displayTxt` . and the result type ID binded to `resultTypeEId`. Select appropriate result type IDs for the scale items that is created. If the result type is 'Dropdown' or 'Multi-Select', the options can be added as array of objects to `dropDownList`.

### Response

The response received with a status code of 200. The response body contained the following data:

``` json
{
   "data": null,
   "errors": null,
   "status": true,
   "errorCode": null,
   "message": "Assessment scale added successfully."
}

 ```
